IT IS ORDERED that Respondent, directly or through any corporation, subsidiary, division, or other device, in connection with the collection of personal information from or about an individual, shall not misrepresent in any manner, expressly or by implication: A. That Respondent will not sell, rent, or loan to third parties such personal information;

B. That Respondent will not provide to any third party personal information about children under the age of thirteen;

C. The manner by which Respondent will notify consumers of changes to its privacy policy; or

D. The manner in which Respondent will collect, use, or disclose personal information.

